review_blob: Pours pitch black, almost no head. Aroma is slightly smokey, roasted malts, dark chocolate.. the typical stuff. Taste is roasted malt, hint of smoke, slight dried dark fruit. After a few sips lots of liquorice shines through. Thick texture. Nice.

Pours black. Dark tan head. Aroma has notes of forest fruits, roasted malt, vanilla, charred oak, coffee. Taste: lots of roasty flavour. Smoked bacon. Wood, medium strong coffee, alcohol, milk chocolate, some scotch influence. Big bodied stout. Good sh*t!
beer_name: Emelisse White Label Coffee Stout (Bruichladdich BA)

review_blob: Light aroma. Fresh hops, pine, citrus. Taste: not much sweetness, very refreshing hoppy taste. Ok stuff.
Not much to say about this. Blonde/pilsner kind of beer with a bit more than average fruity hop notes. Easy drinking. Like it.

One of my favourite imperial stouts. Superb balance. Big body. Typical IRS aroma. Taste: lots of roasted malt, slight vanilla, dark chocolate, wood(sugars), some cream, espresso notes. Great IRS.. pretty easy drinking too.

Big malty and syrupy aroma. Hints of dough, caramel and wood. Taste: great taste. The Auchroisk barrel aging really adds some depth to the standard barley wine flavours. Dried fruit, charred oak, vanilla cream, alcohol, some hops. Nice beer.
Fruity aroma. Almost IPA like. Almost no sweetness. Taste: very refreshing. Lots of carbonation. Spicy bitterness. In your face hoppiness. Good stuff for summer!

Sweet and woody in the aroma. Little bitterness coming through. Taste: very malty, good medium bitterness, some caramel but not too much (hate that), cappucino thing going on too. Pretty full body. Dry aftertaste. Great classic style of beer.

Light stout when looking at the ABV. Aroma is very balanced. Typical roasty, creamy stout. Mouthfeel suprised me. Pretty thick! Tasted creamy, syrup sweetness, roasted malt. Dry aftertaste, as expected. Very decent.

Aroma is pretty light for an imperial stout aged on heavily peated scotch barrels. Roastiness, little peaty, some wood, cream. Taste and mouthfeel was even more dissapointing. Very thin in the mouth. Tasted wood, roasted malts, creamy, some bitterness which felt very off-balance for me. This barrel aging didnt add anything for me when compared to Emelisses regular IRS. Might have to try the Heaven Hill version. Really liked the Ardbeg BA also.
beer_name: Emelisse White Label Imperial Russian Stout (Port Charlotte)

review_blob: Smells very fresh. When pouring a big white head appears. Pineapple, orange, mango. Taste: fresh again, mango from the hops. A little sweetness. Pretty big triple IPA. Nice..

Pours black. Smokey bonfire aroma. Some sweetness in the nose. Roasted malts. Taste: lots of bonfire smoke. Some weird sour note going one. Little sweetness. Some bitter notes. Light bodied. Would have liked the beer a bit more when it had a little more sweetness and bigger body. Ok stuff.
beer_name: De Molen Bloed, Zweet & Tranen (Blood, Sweat & Tears)

review_blob: Hazey amber colour. Very small white head. Pine on the aroma. Oranges. Mango. Taste: not as fruity as the aroma. A bit one dimentional actually. Even picking up some alcohol (?!) Had this one like 4 times before this rating but it still doesnt convince me. Meh-meh. There are so much DIPAs out there that are way better.
Pours pitch black, thick, almost no head. Smells very very roasty, dark fruits, some smoke. Taste: again very roasty. Bitter chocolate. Little smoke. Big booziness. Heavy imperial stout!!
beer_name: To l Long Time No See

review_blob: Weak aroma. Not much going on. Taste: weak stuff. Slighty more power in there than there is in a pilsener. This is not really craftbeer worthy in my opinion. Or am I way too familiar with strong hoppy beers? Whatever..

Hazey amber colour. Very small white head. Piney hop aroma. Little fruity. Taste: very bitter. So much more hop notes present here than in the aroma. Easy drinkable too. Refreshing. Fruity. Good summer IPA.
Nice amber colour. Small white head. Soft aroma. Pine hops, little sweetness. Taste: the rye definitely starts to manifest itself here. Still some pine hops. Big carbonation. Easy drinkable.. Nice.

Very small white head which disappears quickly. Light aroma. Little malty sweetness. Hops coming through but not much fruityness. Taste is pretty bitter even for an IPA. Again, not much fruit. Just hop bitterness. Low ABV and very refreshing. Good.
Black as night. Dark brown head. Aroma of roasted malts, chocolate, milk, wood. Taste: wonderful. Very sweet for an imperial stout, wood, chocolate, roastyness. Full body. Awesome beer.
Looked forward to try this beer. Aroma: coffee, dark chocolate, roasted malt. Taste: lots of coffee, chocolate, good bitterness! Great beer.

Lovely aroma very hop-forward. Taste is more balanced. Nice sweetness and good strong bitterness. Pretty dry finish. Oh and did I mention the looks of this Double IPA? Gorgeous. Cloudy dark amber colour. Good Double IPA.
beer_name: Rooie Dop Ot The Explorer Double IPA

review_blob: Aroma is a little bit peaty, roasted malt, chocolate. Taste: whisky, chocolate, roasted malt, a little boozy though.. Some dark fruits in there also. I love it. Easy drinkable too for 10% abv. Great beer!
Citrus aroma. Some malty sweetness. Mild hoppy taste. Just meh-meh. Expected more from this.
Hoppy aroma. Small head. Taste: mostly hop-forward, dominating citrus notes. Milk, chocolate, roasted malts, bit of coffee, caramel. But yeah, mostly hops. Bitter aftertaste. Good.

Very hazy orange colour when poured from the bottle. Huge head. Sweet malt and citrus aroma. Taste is the same. Some sweet malt and citrus. Good balance but not a great IPA. Killer beer for sunny days though.

Sooo much smoke on the aroma. Earthy peat. Not much else. Taste: good lord this is one hell of a full-bodied stout!! Lots and lots peat. Roasted malts. Little bit of coffee. But damn, so much peat.. Seems almost like a crossbreed between an Islay malt and a coffee stout. Strong stuff. I like it.
beer_name: Emelisse White Label Imperial Russian Stout (Ardbeg BA)

review_blob: Black beer. Big cream coloured head. Light aroma. Some roasted malt, smoke, dark chocolate. Taste: Little bit of sweetness, some roasty notes, lots of mild smoke. Lots of carbonation. Thin body. Average.
Lovely aroma. Lots of chocolate. Some roasted notes. Dark fruits. Some coffee cream. Taste: Very nice. Coffee, milk chocolate, dark fruits, some alcohol.. Lovely stout for sure.

Lovely aroma. Little bit of roasted flavors, some liquorice. Some smoke. Big white head. Taste: a bit disappointing. Not much roasted stuff, almost no smoke. Bit of coffee. Lots of hop flavors which I did not get in the aroma. Decent porter. Not very good.
Very citrus-like aroma with some tropical fruits. Almost no sweetness, just hops hops hops. Taste: Nice tropical bitterness. Very refreshing stuff. Excellent summer IPA.
Black as night. Dark brown head. Roasted and boozy aroma. Taste: coffee, dark chocolate, lots of cognac and too much booze. Meh.. Expected a much better beer. Paid 10 euros for 1 bottle. Overpriced.
beer_name: To l Liquid Confidence (Aged in Cognac Barrels)

review_blob: Nice hazey amber colour, very typical Double IPA. Small white head. Very nice aroma. Fresh tropical fruits. Mango, pineapple, orange. Taste: very hop forward. Not much sweetness. Bitter aftertaste. Still fruity though. Bottle was not as fresh as I hoped for. Decent American IPA.

Very dark brown colour. Not imperial stout-black. Some roasty aromas. Mild coffee. Fresh hops. Not a very strong aroma. Taste: much more hop forward than the aroma initiates. Again mild coffee and roastyness. Little, little bit of sweetness and herbal notes. Long lasting bitter finish.
Dark amber colour. Fruity and medium sweet aroma. Taste is pretty soft, a bit hoppy, balanced. Short finish. OK stuff!

Nice amber colour. Small white head. Not very cloudy unlike some other Double IPA?s. Aroma is decent. Not super duper hop-forward. Some sweetness in the aroma too, which actually did not appear a lot in the taste. Taste: Better than the aroma. Fresh, fruity, strong tongue punching hops! Long lasting bitter aftertaste. Very well known and very good Double IPA. Nice!
Sweet aroma. Tropical fruit. Hints of spice. Taste: Very citrus-like, tropical fruit again. Great hop-bitterness. Little bit of sweet malt flavor. Very solid Double IPA! Love it.

Had a really fresh bottle of this Double IPA. Great fruity aroma. Citrus, grapefruit, orange, pineapple. Some sweetness coming through.
Taste: Sick. Real hop bomb because of the freshness I guess. One of the best Double IPAs Ive ever had. Very, very hop forward but does not feel out of balance at all. Damn. Good stuff!!
beer_name: Uiltje Met Je Cascade Groene Trui

review_blob: Good carbonation. Light beer. Easy drinking. Mediocre aroma. If you like hoppy beer thatll still drink easy as hell; this is a good one. To me, tastes just like a decent Pilsener but instead of classic hops, a nice and light American hop flavour.
UPDATED: MAY 11, 2015
